 This video report reveals that many patients are dying while waiting for cancer treatment in Gauteng public hospitals. First published by GroundUp. <img style="display: none; width: 1px;" src="https://thirdpartyhits.groundup.org.za/counter/hit/dailymaverick/2022-04-12-the-deadly-wait-for-cancer-treatment/" alt="" /> For two years 26-year-old Maria Masetla watched her mother suffer while the health system repeatedly failed them. The cancer in Regina Masetla’s breasts eventually killed her before she could celebrate her 50th birthday with her family in Limpopo. Activists say that Regina’s case is not an isolated one, especially for… Protesters took to Joburg’s inner city demanding that the government stop denying that the city’s key public hospital — Charlotte Maxeke Johannesburg Academic Hospital — is crumbling and pushing cancer treatment backlogs to crisis level. Patients have to wait two months before they can access cancer treatment at Steve Biko Academic Hospital in Pretoria. This is putting their lives at risk. By ORATENG LEPODISE.